==Tips==
Since Events are a limited-time action, and they consist of difficult enemy compositions and maps, it is advised to be prepared for an event before it begins.
* Stockpile {{Fuel}},{{Ammo}},{{Steel}},{{Bauxite}}, and buckets {{IR}}. It is recommended to stock over the auto-regeneration limit (softcap) before the event.
** Buckets are easily obtainable through [[Quests#Daily_Sortie_Quests|Daily Quests]] and [[Expeditions|Expedition]]. Use buckets sparingly before Events to save up.
* Don't rush. If you are new or low on resources, continue to stock up and wait for information on the Event to come to avoid wasting resources on failed attempts.
* Thanks to the ship locking mechanics and branching rules requiring certain ships (Fulfilling it may lead to you easier nodes and/or routes), it's wise to have important historical ships prepared and plan your fleets carefully in advance to make sure they aren't locked prematurely to avoid putting you into a difficult situation. 
* For new players, please read the [[Tutorial:_How_to_Play|Tutorial pages]] first for basic knowledge and refer to the [[Glossary]] and [[Combat|combat mechanics]] pages for ship class abbreviations and understanding of the mechanics used in this game.
